title: WATCH: LeBron gets the steal and the thunderous dunk against Minnesota | NBA | Sporting News
text:
February 1, 2017 8:46pm EST February 1, 2017 8:42pm EST Cavs look like they've got their swagger back. Benyam Kidane 
Published on Feb. 1, 2017 
Feb. 1, 2017 
After their recent slump, the Cavs looks like they've got their swagger back against the Minnesota Timberwolves after a pair of tundering dunks from LeBron James. 
MORE: Cavs interested in Melo if Love not involved 
Intercepting a stray Kriss Dunn pass, LeBron scooped up the ball and flew down the court, soaring towars the rim with the one-handed jam. 
If that wasn;t enough, in the second quarter, he and Kyrie Irving then connected for the sweet alley-oop finish. LeBron gets the steal and the rim rattling dunk! pic.twitter.com/4dGV1JgICP â€” NBA Australia (@NBA_AU) February 2, 2017 
Kyrie enjoyed a productive first half, finishing with 12 points and 10 assists.
